while this is cool, there's also the issue of tanks being hella strong not only in defense but in offense as well, like:

{{champion:32}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:36}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:58}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:72}} {{champion:154}} {{champion:54}} 

I mean, if turrets can't kill them is alright, if they can kill you under turret that cannot be right :S

Take {{champion:89}} for example, she's resilient as hell but she won't be able to dive alone and much less get a kill out of it, That's a good tank! just like {{champion:12}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:27}} {{champion:14}} {{champion:57}}

> Buffing towers buffs sustain/farm champs which slows down game pacing which makes me a sad {{champion:17}} 

Isn't fast game pacing a real problem right now? Seems like a solution to me.... 

[boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/developer-corner/1VymTVKu-game-pacing-and-you](http://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/developer-corner/1VymTVKu-game-pacing-and-you)

The perception that PBE isn't used as a testing grounds makes me really sad :(

We do still put things on the PBE and look for player feedback all the time. I think we could do a way better job of communicating with you guys that we are listening and making decisions based on that feedback. Ultimately it's our failure that players don't feel heard, and we should be better.

One of the problems is that when players confirm what we already thought about something, we don't bump that thread with a "cool, thanks for the input, that's what we were expecting" kind of comment because it doesn't seem very useful. Please keep demanding our attention and keeping us honest! We can always improve {{champion:112}}
